######################################################
                    Installation 
######################################################


Files:
  
 - INSTALL (this documentation file)

 - install.py (installation script)

 - ansible.tgz (tgz file with the contents of /etc/ansible directory)


Prerequisites:

 - Linux CentOS 6

 - Python 2.6 or higuer (not python 3.X)

 - EPEL repository


Installation:

 - Execute install.py. 

 - Operating System and python version will be checked. 

 - If everything is OK 'ansible' software and dependencies will be installed.

 - If 'ansible' installation is OK, '/etc/ansible' directory will be renamed to '/etc/ansible-datetime' and a new '/etc/ansible' directory will be created.

 - Finally 'ansible.tgz' file will be unzipped to '/etc/ansible'
 

Post-Installation:

 - Execute /etc/ansible/menu.py to access the Control Menu. Option '1' to configure System.


######################################################
